<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>Countable/uncountable nouns</title><sectiontitle>Most nouns are countable. They can be singular or plural. </sectiontitle><titlesound>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>I saw the dog.</text1><sound1>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>I saw the &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;dogs.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text1a><text2>I have a child.</text2><sound2>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>I have two &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;children.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2a><titlesound2>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Some nouns are uncountable. They are only singular.</sectiontitle2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>I found some &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;information&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; in this book.</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>The &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;weather&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; is bad.</text4a></section><section><title>Countable/uncountable nouns</title><sectiontitle>With countable nouns, use &lt;I&gt;a/an, a few, some, any, many, a lot of&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_7.mp3</titlesound><text1></text1><sound1>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>She stayed for &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;a few days.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text1a><text2></text2><sound2>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>I don't have &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;many friends.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2a><titlesound2>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_10.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>With uncountable nouns, use &lt;I&gt;a little/a bit of, some, any, much, a lot of&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>Add &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;a little salt.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>Pre-intGRAM_10_2_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>There isn't &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;much traffic.&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text4a></section></grammar>